.TH CP 1
.SH NAME
cp \- copy a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cp
source destination
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B cp
utility copies the contents of the
.I source
file to the
.I destination
file.

No command-line options are supported.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B cp
utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.
.SH SEE ALSO
cat(1)